<teaserTitle>Prosciutto Melon</teaserTitle>
<teaserText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p>On a hot day, you need refreshing starters!</p></div></teaserText>
<detailText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p class="p--heading-2">Introduction</p><p>On a hot day, you need refreshing starters: such one is the Melon with Prosciutto. It could not be easier to prepare! Cut the honey melon with one of our shark knives. Remove the seeds with a spoon and slice into wedges. Wrap with Italian Prosciutto and serve with light, fresh white wine.</p><p class="p--heading-2">Ingredients</p><ul><li>1/4 (350g) rockmelon, seeded</li><li>12 slices prosciutto</li><li>12 fresh basil leaves</li><li>12 cherry bocconcini, drained</li><li>Extra virgin olive oil, to serve</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Preparation</p><ul><li>Using a melon baller or teaspoon, scoop 12 balls from rockmelon</li><li>Fold up each slice of prosciutto into a bundle</li><li>Thread the rockmelon, prosciutto bundles, basil and bocconcini onto skewers</li><li>Drizzle with oil and serve</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Serving Suggestion</p><p>If desired, just before serving, drizzle a tiny (no more than a drop) amount of balsamic vinegar over each piece along with a little coarsely ground black pepper.</p></div></detailText>
